The paper deals with data structures and algorithms for the approximate near neighbor search problem, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry and machine learning. The paper uses techniques from data structures, information theory, computational geometry, and coding theory. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
